# Rebuild & Restart portal after every change

After finishing **any** edit under `portal/` — frontend (`src/`, `vite.config.js`, assets) or backend (`server.js`, `package.json`) — run both steps before telling the user you are done:

## Step 1 — Production build

```bash
cd /Users/tijmendejong/Documents/projects/personal/habbo-agent-platform/portal && npm run build
```

If the build fails, fix all errors and re-run until it passes.

## Step 2 — Restart container

```bash
docker restart agent-portal
```

The `agent-portal` container serves both the built `dist/` (static files) and `server.js` (API). A restart is required to pick up **all** changes — Node.js does not hot-reload.

## Rule

- ✅ Build passes → restart container → tell the user it is done
- ❌ Never mark a task complete without running both steps
- ❌ Never skip the restart even if only frontend files changed
- ❌ **NEVER use `docker compose build`** — the container volume-mounts `./portal/dist` and `./portal/server.js` from the host. Only a local `npm run build` updates the dist the container actually serves. `docker compose build` rebuilds the image but the volume mount overrides it at runtime.
